32#ifndef _SYS_MD5_H_
33#define _SYS_MD5_H_
34
35#include <sys/types.h>
36
37#ifdef HAVE_INTTYPES_H
38#include <inttypes.h>
39#endif
40
41#ifdef HAVE_STDINT_H
42#include <stdint.h>
43#endif
44
45/* iSCSI_MD5 context. */
46typedef struct iSCSI_MD5Context {
47 uint32_t state[4]; /* state (ABCD) */
48 uint32_t count[2]; /* number of bits, modulo 2^64 (lsb first) */
49 unsigned char buffer[64]; /* input buffer */
50} iSCSI_MD5_CTX;
51
52__BEGIN_DECLS
53void iSCSI_MD5Init(iSCSI_MD5_CTX *);
54void iSCSI_MD5Update(iSCSI_MD5_CTX *, const uint8_t *, size_t);
55void iSCSI_MD5Final(unsigned char[16], iSCSI_MD5_CTX *);
56#ifndef _KERNEL
57char *iSCSI_MD5End(iSCSI_MD5_CTX *, char *);
58char *iSCSI_MD5File(const char *, char *);
59char *iSCSI_MD5Data(const uint8_t *, size_t, char *);
60#endif /* _KERNEL */
61__END_DECLS
62
63#endif /* _SYS_MD5_H_ */
